!-----------------------------------------------------------------------
!     Example to evaluate diffsive profile in the inner and outer core
!-----------------------------------------------------------------------
!
Here is the input files to use heat and compositional source terms in Calypso.
To simplify the problem, only the thermal and compositional fields are estimated.

This example consists of the following files and directories

control_MHD:         control file for simulation
control_resolution:  control file for spatial resolution
radial_field.dat:    Input heat and composition source data
result:              example of result data

This example only run with 2 MPI process. The simulation procedure is the following

1. Run simulation program
   [heat_composition_source]$ mpirun -np 1 [CALYPSO_DIR]/bin/sph_mhd
This program makes the following files

radial_point.dat:       radial grid point data
reference_fields.dat:   diffisive profile field data
sph_ave_volume_s.dat:   volume average data
time_total.dat.dat:     elapsed time data